            , and Irish Eliza, was coming down Gray's inn lane, and the prosecutor knocked 
               <persName id="t18150913-181-person1620">
                  Mary 
                  Prior
               <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1620" type="surname" value="Prior"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1620" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1620" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             down. The next day, I saw what passed, and there was a dispute between Irish Eliza and 
               <persName id="t18150913-181-person1621">
                  Mary 
                  Prior
               <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1621" type="surname" value="Prior"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1621" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1621" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , about tearing a gown. The prosecutor said something to Stevens about it, and 
               <persName id="t18150913-181-person1622">
                  Tom 
                  Stevens
               <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1622" type="surname" value="Stevens"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150913-181-person1622" type="given" value="Tom"></interp>
